{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbed4a1db-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s9656"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9656"},"text":"§ 9656.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Transportation of hazardous substances; listing as hazardous material; liability for release","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbed4a1dc-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s9656/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" Each hazardous substance which is listed or designated as provided in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s9601/14"},"text":"section 9601(14) of this title","children":[],"tail":" shall, within 30 days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-17"},"text":"October 17, 1986","children":[],"tail":", or at the time of such listing or designation, whichever is later, be listed and regulated as a hazardous material under chapter 51 of title 49."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idbed4a1dd-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s9656/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" A common or contract carrier shall be liable under other law in lieu of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s9607"},"text":"section 9607 of this title","children":[],"tail":" for damages or remedial action resulting from the release of a hazardous substance during the course of transportation which commenced prior to the effective date of the listing and regulation of such substance as a hazardous material under chapter 51 of title 49, or for substances listed pursuant to subsection (a) of this section, prior to the effective date of such listing: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided, however","children":[],"tail":", That this subsection shall not apply where such a carrier can demonstrate that he did not have actual knowledge of the identity or nature of the substance released."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbed4a1de-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/510/tIII/s306/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–510, title III, § 306(a)","children":[],"tail":", (b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-11"},"text":"Dec. 11, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/2810"},"text":"94 Stat. 2810","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/499/tII/s202"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–499, title II, § 202","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-17"},"text":"Oct. 17, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/1695"},"text":"100 Stat. 1695","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbed4a1df-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbed4a1e0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idbed4a1e1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsecs. (a) and (b), “chapter 51 of title 49” substituted for “the Hazardous Materials Transportation Act [49 App. U.S.C. 1801 et seq.]” on authority of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/272/s6/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–272, § 6(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-07-05"},"text":"July 5, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/1378"},"text":"108 Stat. 1378","children":[],"tail":", the first section of which enacted subtitles II, III, and V to X of Title 49, Transportation."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idbed4a1e2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/499/s202/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–499, § 202(a)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “within 30 days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-17"},"text":"October 17, 1986","children":[],"tail":"” for “within ninety days after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-12-11"},"text":"December 11, 1980","children":[],"tail":"” and inserted “and regulated” before “as a hazardous material”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/499/s202/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–499, § 202(b)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “and regulation” after “prior to the effective date of the listing”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
